Center for Statistical Consulting
Knowable Magazine: “When courtroom science goes wrong — and how stats can fix it” (Hal Stern featured)
October 15, 2018 Bite marks, shoe prints, crime-scene fibers: Matches to suspects are often far shakier than courtroom experts claim. Better statistical methods — among them, a little beast known as the “likelihood ratio” — can cut down on wrong convictions.
Read the full story/comic at Knowable Magazine.

